{"ID":270314, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"314\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs313.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs315.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 314<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">the Gospel of salvation<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> which he revealed? So do I. Christians should cease wrangling and\n  contending<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> with each other, and cultivate the principles of union and friendship in their midst;\n  and they will do it before the millennium can be ushered in and Christ takes possession of His\n  kingdom.<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">&ldquo;Do you believe in the baptism of infants?&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> asks the Presbyterian. No. &ldquo;Why?&rdquo; Because it\n  is nowhere written in the Bible. Circumcision is not baptism,<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> neither was baptism instituted in\n  the place of circumcision. Baptism is for remission of sins.<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> Children have no sins.<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> Jesus blessed\n  them<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> and said, &ldquo;Do what you have seen me do.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> Children are all made alive in Christ,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> and\n  those of riper years through faith and repentance.<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">So far we are agreed with other Christian denominations. They all preach faith and\n  repentance.<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> The gospel<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> requires baptism by immersion for the remission of sins,<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> which is the\n  meaning of the word in the original language&mdash;namely, to bury or immerse.<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Necessity of Ordinances<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">We ask the sects, Do you believe this? They answer, No. I believe in being converted. I believe\n  in this tenaciously. So did the Apostle Peter and the disciples of Jesus.<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> But I further believe in the\n  gift of the Holy Ghost by the laying on of hands.<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> Evidence by Peter&rsquo;s preaching on the day of\n  Pentecost, Acts 2:38.<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> You might as well baptize a bag of sand as a man,<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> if not done in view of\n  the remission of sins and getting of the Holy Ghost.<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> Baptism by water is but half a baptism, and\n  is good for nothing without the other half&mdash;that is, the baptism of the Holy Ghost.<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">The Savior says, &ldquo;Except a man be born of water and of the Spirit, he cannot enter into the\n  kingdom of God.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> &ldquo;Though we or an angel from heaven, preach any other gospel unto you than\n  that which we have preached unto you, let him be accursed,&rdquo; according to Galatians 1:8.<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> (July 9,\n  1843.) DHC 5:498-500.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Discourse&mdash;Burden of the Prophet&rsquo;s Ministry&mdash;Friendship<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">I commence my remarks by reading this text&mdash;Luke 16:16: &ldquo;The law and the prophets were\n  until John: since that time the kingdom of God is preached, and every man presseth into it.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">I do not know that I shall be able to preach much; but,<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115058\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115058)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115058)\">D&amp;C 93:51<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116582\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116582)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116582)\">D&amp;C 136:23<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110767\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110767)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110767)\">Rev. 11:5<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115377\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115377)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115377)\">D&amp;C 105:32<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116247\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116247)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116247)\">D&amp;C 130:9<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112980\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112980)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112980)\">Moro. 8:5-26<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106029\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106029)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106029)\">Gen. 17:10<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108708\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108708)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108708)\">John 7:22-23<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108303\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108303)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108303)\">Mark 1:4<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">7. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112986\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112986)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112986)\">Moro. 8:11<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">8. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108353\"><a